Site classification

Overview

This script was developed to generate streamflow statistics for U.S. Geological Survey (USGS) streamflow data as a part of a RESTORE Act project. The focus of the project is to evaluate streamflow alteration and analyze long-term trends in streams that contribute flow to the Gulf of Mexico.

US Department of the Interior
US Geological Survey

Software

If R (version 3.3 or greater) is not already installed on your computer, download and install the latest binary distribution from the Comprehensive R Archive Network (CRAN). R can also be run from RStudio, which is a nice interface for working with R and provides a console. In order to use RStudio, R must be installed first. The latest version of RStudio is available here. R and RStudio should be accessible from the start menu, a desktop shortcut, or via command shell. Assuming you installed R on a 64-bit operating system (OS), two versions of R are made available, that is, a 32-bit and 64-bit version. The 64-bit version of R (R x64) is preferred.

R will require some packages in order to perform the tasks in the script. The packages can be installed from the console using the code below. The packages dataRetreival and EflowStats were developed by the USGS and provide the tools used in the script to retreive USGS data and compute streamflow statistics.

# add the USGS R repository along with a CRAN mirror
options(repos = c("http://cran.rstudio.com", "http://owi.usgs.gov/R"))
# the p_load function will install packages that are not already installed or
# will activate the libraries for the packages if they are installed
if (!require("pacman")) install.packages("pacman")
pacman::p_load(readr, dataRetrieval, EflowStats, dplyr, lmomco, DT, doParallel, foreach,
               leaflet, rgdal, lubridate)

library(doParallel)

getSiteNo <- function(siteID, siteNm) {
  
  siteID <- isValidID(siteID)
  
  newDF <- data.frame(siteno = as.character(siteID), station_nm = as.character(siteNm), stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
  
  return(newDF)
  
}

cl <- makePSOCKcluster(detectCores() - 4)

clusterEvalQ(cl, library(foreach)); registerDoParallel(cl)

newDF <- foreach(i = 1:nrow(nid_2013), .combine = dplyr::bind_rows, .packages = c("dataRetrieval", "dplyr")) %dopar%
  getSiteNo(siteID = nid_2013[i,14], siteNm = nid_2013[i,15])

stopCluster(cl)

testDF <- nid_2013[,c(14,15)]

forSubsDF <- dplyr::left_join(newDF, testDF, by = "station_nm")

colnames(forSubsDF) <- c("siteno", "station_nm", "SITE_NO")

nid_2013 <- dplyr::left_join(nid_2013, newDF, by = "station_nm", suffix = c("", ".y"))

nid_2013$siteno <- nid_2013$siteno.y

nid_2013 <- dplyr::select(nid_2013, -siteno.y)

extraSites <- LULC_1938[which(!(LULC_1938$SITE_NO %in% testnid_2013$siteno)),]

extraSitesInfo <- function(extraSites) {
  
  df <- data.frame(forSubsDF[0,])
  
  for(i in seq(1, nrow(extraSites), 1)) {
    
    newID <- isValidID(extraSites[i,1])
    
    newInfo <- dataRetrieval::readNWISsite(newID)
    
    newDf <- data.frame(siteno = newID, station_nm = newInfo$station_nm, SITE_NO = extraSites[i,1])
    
    df <- dplyr::bind_rows(df, newDf); rm(newDf)
    
  }
  
  return(df)
  
}

forSubsDF2 <- extraSitesInfo(extraSites)

forSubsDF <- dplyr::bind_rows(forSubsDF, forSubsDF2)

for(i in seq(1, length(lulcList), 1)) {
  
  temp <- readr::read_csv(paste0("D:/Data/restore/BCharacteristicsRESTORE/BCharsRESTORE/", lulcList[i], ".csv"))
  
  temp <- dplyr::left_join(temp, forSubsDF, by = "SITE_NO")
  
  temp$nYear <- str_sub(lulcList[i], 6, 9)
  
  assign(lulcList[i], temp)
  
}

lulc_all <- dplyr::bind_rows(mget(paste0("LULC_", seq(1938, 2004, 1))))

lulc_all[lulc_all == -9999] <- NA

lulc_all$Forest <- rowSums(lulc_all[,c("Deciduous_Forest", "Evergreen_Forest", "Mixed_Forest", "Grassland", "Shrubland")], na.rm = TRUE)

lulc_all$Agri <- rowSums(lulc_all[,c("Cultivated_Cropland", "Hay_Pasture_land")], na.rm = TRUE)

lulc_all$Wetland <- rowSums(lulc_all[,c("Herbaceous_Wetland", "Woody_Wetland")], na.rm = TRUE)

test2004 <- lulc_all %>%
  dplyr::filter(nYear == "2004") %>%
  dplyr::group_by(siteno = siteno) %>%
  dplyr::summarize(Urban = sum(Developed, na.rm = TRUE), 
                   Agri = sum(Agri, na.rm = TRUE),
                   Forest = sum(Forest, na.rm = TRUE),
                   Wetlank = sum(Wetland, na.rm = TRUE))

getTrend <- function(x, start, end) {
  x <- tryCatch( {
    na.interpolation(x)
  },
  error = function(cond) {
    NA
  })
  x <- tryCatch( {
    ts(x, start, end, frequency = 1)
  },
  error = function(cond) {
    NA
  })
  x <- tryCatch( {
    as.numeric(mk.test(x)[6])
  },
  error = function(cond) {
    NA
  })
  x <- signif(x[1], 3)
  return(x)
}

getTrendP <- function(x, start, end) {
  x <- tryCatch( {
    na.interpolation(x)
  },
  error = function(cond) {
    NA
  })
  x <- tryCatch( {
    ts(x, start, end, frequency = 1)
  },
  error = function(cond) {
    NA
  })
  x <- tryCatch( {
    as.numeric(mk.test(x)[5])
  },
  error = function(cond) {
    NA
  })
  x <- signif(x[1], 3)
  return(x)
}

trendTest <- lulc_all %>%
  dplyr::group_by(siteno = siteno) %>%
  dplyr::arrange(as.numeric(nYear)) %>%
  dplyr::summarize(tauUrban = getTrend(Developed, start = 1938, end = 2004), 
                   tauUrbanPVal = getTrendP(Developed, start = 1938, end = 2004),
                   maxUrban = max(Developed, na.rm = TRUE),
                   minUrban = min(Developed, na.rm = TRUE),
                   varUrban = var(Developed, na.rm = TRUE),
                   tauAgri = getTrend(Agri, start = 1938, end = 2004),
                   tauAgriPVal = getTrendP(Agri, start = 1938, end = 2004),
                   maxAgri = max(Agri, na.rm = TRUE),
                   minAgri = min(Agri, na.rm = TRUE),
                   varAgri = var(Agri, na.rm = TRUE),
                   tauForest = getTrend(Forest, start = 1938, end = 2004),
                   tauForestPVal = getTrendP(Forest, start = 1938, end = 2004),
                   maxForest = max(Forest, na.rm = TRUE),
                   minForest = min(Forest, na.rm = TRUE),
                   varForest = var(Forest, na.rm = TRUE),
                   tauWetland = getTrend(Wetland, start = 1938, end = 2004),
                   tauWetlandPVal = getTrendP(Wetland, start = 1938, end = 2004),
                   maxWetland = max(Wetland, na.rm = TRUE),
                   minWetland = min(Wetland, na.rm = TRUE),
                   varWetland = var(Wetland, na.rm = TRUE))

kable(trendTest)

write.csv(trendTest, "data/lulcTrends.csv", row.names = FALSE)

forMap <- trendTest

forMap$station_nm <- NA

forMap$dec_lat_va <- NA

forMap$dec_long_va <- NA

for (i in seq(1, nrow(forMap), 1)) {
  
  info <- readNWISsite(forMap[i,1])
  
  info <- info[1,]
  
  forMap[i,22] <- info$station_nm
  
  forMap[i,23] <- info$dec_lat_va
  
  forMap[i,24] <- info$dec_long_va
  
  rm(info)
  
}

write.csv(forMap, "data/forMap.csv", row.names = FALSE)

Map trends in development

pacman::p_load(dataRetrieval, leaflet)

forMap <- readr::read_csv("data/forMap.csv")

forMapUrb <- dplyr::filter(forMap, !is.na(tauUrban))

m <- leaflet::leaflet()

grp <- c("USGS Topo", "USGS Imagery Only", "USGS Imagery Topo",
         "USGS Shaded Relief", "Hydrography")

att <- paste0("<a href='https://www.usgs.gov/'>",
              "U.S. Geological Survey</a> | ",
              "<a href='https://www.usgs.gov/laws/policies_notices.html'>",
              "Policies</a>")

GetURL <- function(service, host = "basemap.nationalmap.gov") {
  sprintf("https://%s/arcgis/services/%s/MapServer/WmsServer", host, service)
}

m <- leaflet::addWMSTiles(m, GetURL("USGSTopo"),
                          group = grp[1], attribution = att, layers = "0")

m <- leaflet::addWMSTiles(m, GetURL("USGSImageryOnly"),
                          group = grp[2], attribution = att, layers = "0")

m <- leaflet::addWMSTiles(m, GetURL("USGSImageryTopo"),
                          group = grp[3], attribution = att, layers = "0")

m <- leaflet::addWMSTiles(m, GetURL("USGSShadedReliefOnly"),
                          group = grp[4], attribution = att, layers = "0")

opt <- leaflet::WMSTileOptions(format = "image/png", transparent = TRUE)

m <- leaflet::addWMSTiles(m, GetURL("USGSHydroCached"),
                          group = grp[5], options = opt, layers = "0")

m <- leaflet::hideGroup(m, grp[5])

sp::coordinates(forMapUrb) <- c("dec_long_va", "dec_lat_va")

sp::proj4string(forMapUrb) <- sp::CRS("+proj=longlat +datum=NAD83")

forMapUrb <- sp::spTransform(forMapUrb, sp::CRS("+init=epsg:4326"))

num <- forMapUrb$siteno  # site number
nam <- forMapUrb$station_nm # local site name
tauUrb <- forMapUrb$tauUrban
minUrb <- forMapUrb$minUrban
maxUrb <- forMapUrb$maxUrban
url <- sprintf("https://waterdata.usgs.gov/nwis/inventory/?site_no=%s", num)
pop <- sprintf("<b>Name:</b> %s<br/><b>Site No:</b> <a href='%s'>%s</a><br/><b>Tau:</b> %s<br/><b>Min:</b> %s<br/><b>Max:</b> %s<br/>",
               nam, url, num, tauUrb, minUrb, maxUrb)

#opt <- leaflet::markerClusterOptions(showCoverageOnHover = TRUE)

getColor <- function(forMapUrb) {
  sapply(forMapUrb$tauUrban, function(tauUrban) {
  if(tauUrban <= -0.1) {
    "green"
  } else if(tauUrban > -0.1 & tauUrban < 0.1) {
    "orange"
  } else {
    "red"
  } })
}

icons <- leaflet::awesomeIcons(
  icon = 'ios-plus',
  iconColor = 'black',
  library = 'ion',
  markerColor = getColor(forMapUrb[1:nrow(forMapUrb),])
)

#m <- leaflet::addCircleMarkers(m, radius = 5, weight = 3, popup = pop, data = forMapUrb)

m <- leaflet::addAwesomeMarkers(m, icon = icons, popup = pop, data = forMapUrb)

opt <- leaflet::layersControlOptions(collapsed = TRUE)

m <- leaflet::addLayersControl(m, baseGroups = grp[1:4],
                               overlayGroups = grp[5], options = opt)

m
